SUMMARY:after work bike ride on the ATT 
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\nI know that it’s hard to imagine\, given the weather we’ve had from. Mid January to almost mid February\, but it’s time to prepare for the 2026 season of the Tuesday after work bike rides. This seasonal\, weekly event has been going on since 2011! It will begin with just over 1 hour of riding\, and as the days get longer we’ll increase the ride time and distance tracking sunset.\nWe'll be starting near Southpoint and final starting point will be sent out Monday evening. Make sure that your bike is in good working order - tires hold air and are up to pressure\, brakes and shifters work and your chain has been oiled. We'll be riding just about 1 hours and about 12 miles. The ride is fairly flat and shaded and our pace will be moderate (about 13 mph average). I recommend a hard tail or hybrid bike\, but if you really want to bring a road bike it's ok\, though you'll likely be a bit bored. Unicycles....? I'll be eating after the ride at a restaurant. You're welcome to join me if you like. Helmets are required and by signing up you agree to THOG liability waiver statement. Please Note!! Any cancellation less than 30 hours before the beginning of the event will be considered a "no show"
